title: Techtonic shift: GCCs hiring 4x faster than IT cos now
description: GCCs are expanding headcount by 18-27% year on year, compared with 4-6% for IT services, according to data from staffing firm TeamLease Digital. Together, they employ nearly 2 million people now, up from 1.2 million in 2022, creating about 300,000 jobs annually. In contrast, IT services have added only 25,000-40,000 employees a year on a net basis during this period.

title: In IT services market, nimble midsize cos gain over large caps
description: Brokerage BNP Paribas in a report said key mid- and small-cap firms’ market share grew by 22 basis points (0.22 percentage point) from a year earlier in the first half when the top six India-based IT services companies lost an aggregate 40 bps.

title: Bharti Singh details her ‘automatic’ intermittent fasting routine, breakfast, dinner timings: ‘White butter, paratha, and black tea...’
description: Comedian Bharti Singh shared her successful experience with intermittent fasting (IF), maintaining a 16-hour fasting window from 7 PM to 10 AM daily, followed by a "proper breakfast thali" and then dinner at 7 PM. Dt. Vaishali Verma, a consultant in nutrition and dietetics, explains that IF, particularly the popular 16/8 method, involves cycling between eating and fasting periods, shifting the body from sugar to stored fat for energy. When done correctly, IF can lead to weight loss, improved blood sugar control, and reduced inflammation. While generally suitable for most healthy adults, Verma emphasizes consulting a doctor before starting, especially for individuals with underlying health conditions, pregnant or breastfeeding women, or those with a history of eating disorders. During the fasting window, non-caloric drinks like water, black coffee, or unsweetened tea are permitted, and it's crucial to listen to one's body and break the fast if feeling unwell.

title: Armed with new RBI approvals, HSBC India's Hitendra Dave wants a seat at the big banks' table
description: HSBC India's CEO Hitendra Dave plans to expand the bank's presence by opening 20 new branches after receiving RBI approval.
